{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, a single host device is used for score calculation, resulting in many-to-one traffic.",
    "We see a similar scenario for 𝐾, 𝑄 and 𝑉 since HBM is utilized for determining 𝐾 and 𝑄 values, whereas 𝑉 is computed on SRAM cores [26].",
    "In contrast, Atleus utilizes an integrated 3D architecture using vertical links to enable efficient communication among the heterogeneous cores.Further, we see higher computation time for HAIMA in comparison to Atleus.",
    "As mentioned earlier, the pipelined architecture executes transformer encoder/decoder layers concurrently across different stages.",
    "However, the HBM design limits the number of parallel bank accesses for power management purpose [58]."
  ]
}